{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847564306,"sessionID":"ses_2873cd7b1ffeRde6iqnPK1xQvg","part":{"id":"prt_d78c35ced001rdjJemts9rNYfh","messageID":"msg_d78c3456c001AD59LdJhK4zBu1","sessionID":"ses_2873cd7b1ffeRde6iqnPK1xQvg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-cc276b9a9d8942678cfc3a98cd1b63f2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The WorkloadManager package provides the HTTP service framework for managing AgentCube sandbox lifecycles on Kubernetes. It orchestrates sandbox creation, deletion, garbage collection, and health monitoring through a layered architecture combining Kubernetes dynamic client operations with an in-memory store for session tracking.\n14: \n15: ## Design\n16: \n17: ### Architecture\n18: \n19: ```\n20: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n21: │                          HTTPServer                                  │\n22: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────┐ │\n23: │  │   Router    │  │ Middleware   │  │         Handlers            │ │\n24: │  │  (chi/v5)   │  │ Recovery     │  │ DeletionHandler             │ │\n25: │  │             │  │ Logging      │  │ HealthHandler               │ │\n26: │  │             │  │ CORS         │  │ HandlerFuncAdapter          │ │\n27: │  └─────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────┘ │\n28: │                               │                                      │\n29: │  ┌────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────────┐ │\n30: │  │                    SandboxLifecycleManager                       │ │\n31: │  │  - DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)                                 │ │\n32: │  │  - ForceDeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)                            │ │\n33: │  │  - IsExpired(sandbox)                                            │ │\n34: │  │  - IsIdleExpired(sandbox, timeout)                               │ │\n35: │  │  - GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID)                                    │ │\n36: │  │  - UpdateSandboxStatus(ctx, sessionID, status)                  │ │\n37: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n38: │                               │                                      │\n39: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────┐│\n40: │  │ GarbageCollector │  │   K8sClient  │  │       MemoryStore       ││\n41: │  │ - runLoop()      │  │ dynamicClient│  │ - StoreSandbox()        ││\n42: │  │ - runOnce()      │  │ coreClient   │  │ - GetSandboxBySessionID ││\n43: │  │ - Start/Stop     │  │ podLister    │  │ - UpdateSandbox()       ││\n44: │  │                  │  │ informerFact │  │ - DeleteSandboxBySession││\n45: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────┘  │ - ListExpiredSandboxes  ││\n46: │                        ┌──────────────┐  │ - ListInactiveSandboxes ││\n47: │                        │  Informers   │  └─────────────────────────┘│\n48: │                        │ factory      │                              │\n49: │                        │ Start/Wait   │                              │\n50: │                        └──────────────┘                              │\n51: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: **Component Responsibilities:**\n55: \n56: | Component | Responsibility |\n57: |-----------|---------------|\n58: | `HTTPServer` | HTTP lifecycle management, graceful shutdown, handler registration |\n59: | `Router` | Chi router wrapper for route registration |\n60: | `Middleware` | Recovery, logging, CORS handling for all requests |\n61: | `Handlers` | HTTP endpoint implementation for sandbox operations |\n62: | `SandboxLifecycleManager` | Core sandbox lifecycle orchestration (create/delete/status) |\n63: | `GarbageCollector` | Background cleanup of expired/idle sandboxes |\n64: | `K8sClient` | Kubernetes client wrapper with dynamic/client-go/informers |\n65: | `Informers` | SharedInformerFactory for pod watching |\n66: | `MemoryStore` | In-memory session tracking with expiration indices |\n67: | `ClientCache` | Token-scoped dynamic client caching for multi-tenant access |\n68: \n69: ### Dependencies\n70: \n71: | Package | Purpose |\n72: |---------|---------|\n73: | `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | HTTP routing |\n74: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes client |\n75: | `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | Dynamic client for CRD operations |\n76: | `k8s.io/client-go/informers` | SharedInformerFactory for caching |\n77: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | K8s API error handling |\n78: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Controller utilities |\n79: \n80: ## Data Structures\n81: \n82: ### Core Types\n83: \n84: ```go\n85: type SandboxInfo struct {\n86:     Kind               string              // AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter/Sandbox/SandboxClaim\n87:     SandboxID          string              // Unique sandbox identifier\n88:     SandboxNamespace   string              // K8s namespace\n89:     SandboxName        string              // K8s resource name\n90:     Name               string              // Runtime name\n91:     SessionID          string              // Session identifier (primary key)\n92:     CreatedAt          time.Time           // Creation timestamp\n93:     ExpiresAt          time.Time           // Expiration timestamp\n94:     Status             string              // Current status\n95:     EntryPoints        []SandboxEntryPoint // Network entry points\n96:     UserToken          string              // User authentication token\n97:     ServiceAccount     string              // K8s service account\n98:     ServiceAccountName string              // Service account name\n99:     LastActivity       time.Time           // Last activity timestamp\n100: }\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ### Error Types\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: type ValidationError struct {\n107:     Field  string\n108:     Reason string\n109: }\n110: \n111: type NotFoundError struct {\n112:     Resource string\n113:     Name     string\n114: }\n115: \n116: type InternalError struct {\n117:     Err error\n118: }\n119: \n120: type ServiceUnavailableError struct {\n121:     Dependency string\n122: }\n123: \n124: type ConflictError struct {\n125:     Resource string\n126:     Err      error\n127: }\n128: ```\n129: \n130: ### Configuration Types\n131: \n132: ```go\n133: type Config struct {\n134:     Addr            string        // \":8080\"\n135:     ReadTimeout     time.Duration // 15s\n136:     WriteTimeout    time.Duration // 15s\n137:     IdleTimeout     time.Duration // 60s\n138:     ShutdownTimeout time.Duration // 30s\n139:     EnableHealthz   bool\n140:     EnableReadyz    bool\n141: }\n142: \n143: type LifecycleConfig struct {\n144:     DefaultTTL          time.Duration // 8h\n145:     DefaultIdleTimeout  time.Duration // 15m\n146:     DefaultMaxDuration  time.Duration // 8h\n147:     GCInterval          time.Duration // 2m\n148:     GCOnceTimeout       time.Duration // 2m\n149:     DeletionGracePeriod int64         // 0\n150:     DeletionTimeout     time.Duration // 30s\n151: }\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ### Constants and GVR\n155: \n156: ```go\n157: const (\n158:     DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n159:     DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n160:     DefaultMaxSessionDuration = 8 * time.Hour\n161:     SandboxCreationTimeout    = 2 * time.Minute\n162:     SandboxDeleteTimeout      = 30 * time.Second\n163:     InformerSyncTimeout       = 1 * time.Minute\n164:     GarbageCollectorInterval  = 2 * time.Minute\n165:     GCBatchSize               = 16\n166: )\n167: \n168: var SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n169:     Group:    \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n170:     Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n171:     Resource: \"sandboxes\",\n172: }\n173: \n174: var SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n175:     Group:    \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\",\n176:     Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n177:     Resource: \"sandboxclaims\",\n178: }\n179: ```\n180: \n181: ### Labels and Annotations\n182: \n183: ```go\n184: const (\n185:     LabelKeySessionID    = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n186:     LabelKeyWorkloadName = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n187:     LabelKeySandboxName  = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n188:     LabelKeyManagedBy    = \"managed-by\"\n189:     ManagedByValue       = \"agentcube-workload-manager\"\n190:     \n191:     AnnotationKeyIdleTimeout = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n192:     AnnotationKeyPodName     = \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"\n193: )\n194: ```\n195: \n196: ## API Endpoints\n197: \n198: ### Sandbox Deletion\n199: \n200: | Method | Path | Description |\n201: |--------|------|-------------|\n202: | DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/{sessionId}` | Delete AgentRuntime sandbox |\n203: | DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{sessionId}` | Delete CodeInterpreter sandbox |\n204: \n205: **Request:**\n206: - `sessionId` (path parameter) - Required\n207: - `force` (optional) - Force deletion with gracePeriod=0\n208: - `gracePeriodSeconds` (optional) - Deletion grace period\n209: \n210: **Response (200):**\n211: ```json\n212: {\n213:     \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n214:     \"status\": \"deleted\"\n215: }\n216: ```\n217: \n218: **Response (404):**\n219: ```json\n220: {\n221:     \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n222:     \"status\": \"not_found\",\n223:     \"message\": \"not found: sandbox/session-123\"\n224: }\n225: ```\n226: \n227: ### Health Endpoints\n228: \n229: | Method | Path | Description |\n230: |--------|------|-------------|\n231: | GET | `/healthz` | Basic health check |\n232: | GET | `/readyz` | Readiness check (informers sync) |\n233: \n234: ## Error Handling\n235: \n236: ### Error Classification\n237: \n238: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Code |\n239: |------------|-------------|------|\n240: | `ValidationError` | 400 | VALIDATION_ERROR |\n241: | `NotFoundError` | 404 | NOT_FOUND |\n242: | `ServiceUnavailableError` | 503 | SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE |\n243: | `ConflictError` | 409 | (via K8s API) |\n244: | `InternalError` | 500 | INTERNAL_ERROR |\n245: \n246: ### HandleError Function\n247: \n248: ```go\n249: func HandleError(w http.ResponseWriter, _ *http.Request, err error) {\n250:     w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n251:     \n252:     var resp ErrorResponse\n253:     var status int\n254:     \n255:     switch e := err.(type) {\n256:     case *ValidationError:\n257:         status = http.StatusBadRequest\n258:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"VALIDATION_ERROR\", Message: \"Invalid request parameter\", ...}\n259:     case *NotFoundError:\n260:         status = http.StatusNotFound\n261:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"NOT_FOUND\", Message: e.Error()}\n262:     case *ServiceUnavailableError:\n263:         status = http.StatusServiceUnavailable\n264:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\", ...}\n265:     case *InternalError:\n266:         status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n267:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", Message: \"Unexpected server error\"}\n268:     default:\n269:         status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n270:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", Message: \"Unexpected server error\"}\n271:     }\n272:     \n273:     w.WriteHeader(status)\n274:     json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(resp)\n275: }\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ### K8s API Error Handling\n279: \n280: ```go\n281: func handleDeleteError(err error) error {\n282:     if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n283:         return nil  // Already deleted, success\n284:     }\n285:     if apierrors.IsConflict(err) {\n286:         return &ConflictError{Resource: \"sandbox\", Err: err}\n287:     }\n288:     return &InternalError{Err: err}\n289: }\n290: ```\n291: \n292: ## Testing Strategy\n293: \n294: ### Test Patterns\n295: \n296: 1. **Unit Tests** - Each component tested independently with mocks\n297: 2. **Fake K8s Clients** - `dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient`, `fake.NewSimpleClientset`\n298: 3. **Mock Logger** - Simple struct capturing Info/Error calls\n299: 4. **Test Informer Factory** - `NewTestInformerFactory` for controlled sync\n300: \n301: ### Test Helpers\n302: \n303: ```go\n304: type mockLogger struct {\n305:     infoCalls  []string\n306:     errorCalls []string\n307: }\n308: \n309: func (l *mockLogger) Info(msg string, args ...any) {\n310:     l.infoCalls = append(l.infoCalls, msg)\n311: }\n312: \n313: func (l *mockLogger) Error(msg string, args ...any) {\n314:     l.errorCalls = append(l.errorCalls, msg)\n315: }\n316: \n317: func NewTestInformerFactory(client kubernetes.Interface) informers.SharedInformerFactory {\n318:     return informers.NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, time.Minute)\n319: }\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### Test Coverage Areas\n323: \n324: | File | Test Coverage |\n325: |------|---------------|\n326: | `lifecycle_test.go` | DeleteSandbox, ForceDeleteSandbox, IsExpired, IsIdleExpired, GetSandbox, UpdateSandboxStatus |\n327: | `k8s_client_test.go` | NewK8sClient, StartInformers, WaitForCacheSync, PodLister, ClientCache |\n328: | `store_test.go` | StoreSandbox, GetSandboxBySessionID, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandbox, ListExpired/Inactive |\n329: | `garbage_collector_test.go` | runOnce, Start/Stop, idle timeout behavior |\n330: | `handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go` | HTTP deletion endpoints, error handling |\n331: | `server_test.go` | Start/Stop, GracefulShutdown, handler registration |\n332: \n333: ### Integration Test Strategy\n334: \n335: ```go\n336: func TestIntegration_ServerLifecycle(t *testing.T) {\n337:     scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n338:     dynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(scheme)\n339:     fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n340:     informerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n341:     \n342:     k8sClient := &K8sClient{\n343:         dynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n344:         coreClient:      fakeClient,\n345:         informerFactory: informerFactory,\n346:     }\n347:     \n348:     store := NewMemoryStore()\n349:     logger := &mockLogger{}\n350:     cfg := DefaultConfig()\n351:     \n352:     server := NewHTTPServerWithClients(cfg, logger, k8sClient, store)\n353:     \n354:     // Register handlers, start server, verify endpoints\n355: }\n356: ```\n357: \n358: ## Validation Checklist\n359: \n360: - [x] HTTPServer graceful shutdown with context timeout\n361: - [x] K8sClient with dynamic/client-go/informers integration\n362: - [x] MemoryStore with expiration and activity indices\n363: - [x] GarbageCollector background cleanup loop\n364: - [x] SandboxLifecycleManager handles Sandbox + SandboxClaim deletion\n365: - [x] Error classification with structured JSON responses\n366: - [x] DeletionReason enum for tracking cleanup triggers\n367: - [x] ClientCache for multi-tenant token-scoped clients\n368: - [x] Chi router with middleware chain (Recovery → Logging → CORS)\n369: \n370: ## Open Questions\n371: \n372: - Q: Should Store interface support persistent backend (Redis/etcd)?\n373:   - A: MemoryStore is current implementation; Store interface allows future extension\n374: \n375: - Q: Should AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter informers watch CR status changes?\n376:   - A: Current implementation uses Pod informers; CR informers can be added via client-go generated informers\n377: \n378: - Q: Should GarbageCollector emit metrics for deletion counts/reasons?\n379:   - A: Not implemented yet; can be added via Prometheus integration\n380: \n381: ## References\n382: \n383: - `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/` - Generated client-go for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n384: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go` - AgentRuntime CRD definition\n385: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` - CodeInterpreter CRD definition\n386: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` - Shared types, labels, annotations, conditions\n387: - `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` - SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response\n388: - `deployment/client-go.md` - Client-go library documentation\n\n(End of file - total 388 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe WorkloadManager package provides the HTTP service framework for managing AgentCube sandbox lifecycles on Kubernetes. It orchestrates sandbox creation, deletion, garbage collection, and health monitoring through a layered architecture combining Kubernetes dynamic client operations with an in-memory store for session tracking.\n\n## Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/design.md","time":{"start":1775847564273,"end":1775847564304}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847564308,"sessionID":"ses_2873cd7b1ffeRde6iqnPK1xQvg","part":{"id":"prt_d78c363d4001qFnLtB9oB45NEf","messageID":"msg_d78c3456c001AD59LdJhK4zBu1","sessionID":"ses_2873cd7b1ffeRde6iqnPK1xQvg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-347401cf3c30429b8e53e0428af97233","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the Kubernetes Reconciler controller that watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources, maintains desired state by managing sandbox pods, updates resource status conditions, and integrates with the informer framework from the generated client-go library.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Reconciler type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `Reconciler` as a Kubernetes controller for reconciling AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Reconciler struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `Reconciler` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `client clientset.Interface` for typed Kubernetes API access (from `client-go/clientset/versioned`)\n26:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for core Kubernetes API\n27:   - `store Store` for sandbox state persistence\n28:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n29:   - `namespace string` for default namespace\n30:   - `scheme *runtime.Scheme` for encoding/decoding resources\n31:   - `recorder record.EventRecorder` for Kubernetes events\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: NewReconciler constructor\n34: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n35: - **WHEN** calling `NewReconciler(client clientset.Interface, kubeClient kubernetes.Interface, store Store, logger Logger, namespace string, scheme *runtime.Scheme, recorder record.EventRecorder)`\n36: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*Reconciler` with all fields initialized\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Informer integration\n41: \n42: The system SHALL use informers from client-go library to watch custom resources.\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime informer setup\n45: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n46: - **WHEN** initializing the reconciler\n47: - **THEN** `SharedInformerFactory` from `client-go/informers/externalversions` SHALL be used\n48: - AND `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()` SHALL be accessed for AgentRuntime watching\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter informer setup\n51: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n52: - **WHEN** initializing the reconciler\n53: - **THEN** `SharedInformerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()` SHALL be accessed for CodeInterpreter watching\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Informer event handlers\n56: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter informers\n57: - **WHEN** setting up event handlers\n58: - **THEN** `AddFunc`, `UpdateFunc`, `DeleteFunc` SHALL be registered on each informer\n59: - AND each handler SHALL call `Reconciler.Reconcile(ctx, key)` with the resource key\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Informer Start\n62: - **GIVEN** a configured `SharedInformerFactory`\n63: - **WHEN** calling `factory.Start(stopCh)`\n64: - **THEN** all informers SHALL begin watching resources\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: WaitForCacheSync\n67: - **GIVEN** a started informer factory\n68: - **WHEN** calling `factory.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)`\n69: - **THEN** it SHALL return `map[reflect.Type]bool` indicating sync status\n70: - AND all types SHALL be `true` before reconciliation begins\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ### Requirement: Reconcile method\n75: \n76: The system SHALL implement the Reconcile method to process resource changes.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Reconcile method signature\n79: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n80: - **WHEN** reading the `Reconcile` method\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL have signature `Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)`\n82: - AND SHALL implement `reconcile.Reconciler` interface from `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime`\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Reconcile parses request key\n85: - **GIVEN** a `reconcile.Request` with `Namespace=\"default\"` and `Name=\"my-runtime\"`\n86: - **WHEN** processing the reconcile request\n87: - **THEN** the reconciler SHALL use `req.Namespace` and `req.Name` to fetch the resource\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Reconcile fetches AgentRuntime\n90: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request for an AgentRuntime\n91: - **WHEN** processing the request\n92: - **THEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called\n93: - AND the returned `AgentRuntime` SHALL be used for reconciliation\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Reconcile fetches CodeInterpreter\n96: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request for a CodeInterpreter\n97: - **WHEN** processing the request\n98: - **THEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called\n99: - AND the returned `CodeInterpreter` SHALL be used for reconciliation\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Reconcile handles not found\n102: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request for a deleted resource\n103: - **WHEN** `Get` returns `IsNotFound` error\n104: - **THEN** reconciliation SHALL return `reconcile.Result{}` with no error\n105: - AND cleanup logic SHALL be triggered if needed\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Status update\n110: \n111: The system SHALL update status conditions on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Update AgentRuntime status\n114: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with updated conditions\n115: - **WHEN** calling status update\n116: - **THEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})` SHALL be called\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Update CodeInterpreter status\n119: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with updated conditions\n120: - **WHEN** calling status update\n121: - **THEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).UpdateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.UpdateOptions{})` SHALL be called\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Set Ready condition\n124: - **GIVEN** a runtime that is ready to serve\n125: - **WHEN** updating status\n126: - **THEN** condition `ConditionTypeReady` SHALL be set with:\n127:   - `Type: \"Ready\"`\n128:   - `Status: metav1.ConditionTrue`\n129:   - `Reason: ConditionReasonRunning`\n130:   - `Message: \"Runtime is ready\"`\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Set Progressing condition\n133: - **GIVEN** a runtime being created or updated\n134: - **WHEN** updating status\n135: - **THEN** condition `ConditionTypeProgressing` SHALL be set with:\n136:   - `Type: \"Progressing\"`\n137:   - `Status: metav1.ConditionTrue`\n138:   - `Reason: ConditionReasonCreating` or `ConditionReasonUpdating`\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: Set Degraded condition\n141: - **GIVEN** a runtime with errors\n142: - **WHEN** updating status\n143: - **THEN** condition `ConditionTypeDegraded` SHALL be set with:\n144:   - `Type: \"Degraded\"`\n145:   - `Status: metav1.ConditionTrue`\n146:   - `Reason: ConditionReasonError`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Set Available condition\n149: - **GIVEN** a runtime with active pods\n150: - **WHEN** updating status\n151: - **THEN** condition `ConditionTypeAvailable` SHALL be set with:\n152:   - `Type: \"Available\"`\n153:   - `Status: metav1.ConditionTrue`\n154:   - `Reason: ConditionReasonRunning`\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ### Requirement: Lister usage\n159: \n160: The system SHALL use listers from client-go for efficient resource lookup.\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime lister\n163: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n164: - **WHEN** using the AgentRuntime lister\n165: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeLister` from `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1` SHALL be used\n166: - AND `lister.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(name)` SHALL return cached AgentRuntime\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter lister\n169: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n170: - **WHEN** using the CodeInterpreter lister\n171: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterLister` from `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1` SHALL be used\n172: - AND `lister.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(name)` SHALL return cached CodeInterpreter\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Pod lister for sandbox lookup\n175: - **GIVEN** a reconciler looking for sandbox pods\n176: - **WHEN** searching for pods owned by a runtime\n177: - **THEN** `corev1listers.PodLister` SHALL be used\n178: - AND `lister.Pods(namespace).List(selector)` SHALL return pods matching label selector\n179: \n180: ---\n181: \n182: ### Requirement: Warm pool reconciler for CodeInterpreter\n183: \n184: The system SHALL maintain warm pool pods for CodeInterpreter resources.\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: Warm pool size check\n187: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize=5`\n188: - **WHEN** reconciling\n189: - **THEN** the reconciler SHALL count existing warm pool pods\n190: - AND pods with annotation `AnnotationKeyWarmPoolMember=\"true\"` SHALL be counted\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Create warm pool pod\n193: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize > currentWarmPoolCount`\n194: - **WHEN** reconciling\n195: - **THEN** new warm pool pods SHALL be created\n196: - AND annotation `AnnotationKeyWarmPoolMember` SHALL be set to `\"true\"`\n197: - AND label `LabelKeyOwnerRuntime` SHALL be set to CodeInterpreter name\n198: - AND label `LabelKeyOwnerKind` SHALL be set to `\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Delete excess warm pool pods\n201: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize < currentWarmPoolCount`\n202: - **WHEN** reconciling\n203: - **THEN** excess warm pool pods SHALL be deleted\n204: - AND pods SHALL be selected based on oldest creation timestamp\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Warm pool pod spec\n207: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter template\n208: - **WHEN** creating warm pool pod\n209: - **THEN** pod spec SHALL be derived from `CodeInterpreter.Spec.Template`\n210: - AND `Image` SHALL be from `Template.Image`\n211: - AND `RuntimeClassName` SHALL be from `Template.RuntimeClassName` if set\n212: \n213: ---\n214: \n215: ### Requirement: Event recording\n216: \n217: The system SHALL record Kubernetes events for resource lifecycle.\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Record created event\n220: - **GIVEN** a newly created AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n221: - **WHEN** reconciliation succeeds\n222: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Normal\", \"Created\", \"Runtime created successfully\")` SHALL be called\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: Record Updated event\n225: - **GIVEN** an updated AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n226: - **WHEN** reconciliation succeeds\n227: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Normal\", \"Updated\", \"Runtime updated successfully\")` SHALL be called\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Record Error event\n230: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation error\n231: - **WHEN** error occurs\n232: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Warning\", \"Error\", errorMessage)` SHALL be called\n233: \n234: #### Scenario: Record SessionStarted event\n235: - **GIVEN** a runtime with active session\n236: - **WHEN** session starts\n237: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Normal\", \"SessionStarted\", \"Session started\")` SHALL be called\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: Record SessionEnded event\n240: - **GIVEN** a runtime with ended session\n241: - **WHEN** session ends\n242: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Normal\", \"SessionEnded\", \"Session ended: <reason>\")` SHALL be called\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ### Requirement: Reconcile loop control\n247: \n248: The system SHALL control reconcile loop timing and retries.\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: Requeue on error\n251: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation that returns error\n252: - **WHEN** processing result\n253: - **THEN** `reconcile.Result{Requeue: true, RequeueAfter: ReconcileErrorRetryInterval}` SHALL be returned\n254: - AND default retry interval SHALL be `1 * time.Minute`\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: Requeue for periodic check\n257: - **GIVEN** a successful reconciliation\n258: - **WHEN** periodic status check is needed\n259: - **THEN** `reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: ReconcilePeriodicInterval}` SHALL be returned\n260: - AND default periodic interval SHALL be `5 * time.Minute`\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: No requeue on completion\n263: - **GIVEN** a resource that is fully reconciled\n264: - **WHEN** no further action is needed\n265: - **THEN** `reconcile.Result{}` SHALL be returned\n266: \n267: ---\n268: \n269: ### Requirement: Controller setup\n270: \n271: The system SHALL provide controller setup and management functions.\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: ControllerManager setup\n274: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller.go`\n275: - **WHEN** reading the setup\n276: - **THEN** `SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager)` SHALL be implemented\n277: - AND SHALL use `ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).Complete(r)` pattern\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Watches setup for AgentRuntime\n280: - **GIVEN** controller setup for AgentRuntime\n281: - **WHEN** configuring watches\n282: - **THEN** `For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{})` SHALL be called\n283: - AND `Owns(&corev1.Pod{})` SHALL be called for owned pods\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: Watches setup for CodeInterpreter\n286: - **GIVEN** controller setup for CodeInterpreter\n287: - **WHEN** configuring watches\n288: - **THEN** `For(&runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{})` SHALL be called\n289: - AND `Owns(&corev1.Pod{})` SHALL be called for owned pods\n290: \n291: ---\n292: \n293: ### Requirement: Resource deletion handling\n294: \n295: The system SHALL handle resource deletion gracefully.\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime deletion\n298: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime being deleted\n299: - **WHEN** reconciling with deletion timestamp set\n300: - **THEN** all sandbox pods owned by the runtime SHALL be deleted\n301: - AND status SHALL be updated with `ConditionReasonDeleting`\n302: \n303: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter deletion\n304: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter being deleted\n305: - **WHEN** reconciling with deletion timestamp set\n306: - **THEN** all sandbox pods and warm pool pods SHALL be deleted\n307: - AND status SHALL be updated with `ConditionReasonDeleting`\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Deletion cleanup\n310: - **GIVEN** a deleted runtime\n311: - **WHEN** all pods are deleted\n312: - **THEN** store entries SHALL be removed for associated sandboxes\n313: - AND finalizer SHALL be removed if present\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ### Requirement: Finalizer handling\n318: \n319: The system SHALL use finalizers for cleanup before deletion.\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: Add finalizer on creation\n322: - **GIVEN** a newly created AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n323: - **WHEN** reconciling for the first time\n324: - **THEN** finalizer `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer` SHALL be added to metadata.finalizers\n325: \n326: #### Scenario: Process finalizer on deletion\n327: - **GIVEN** a runtime with deletion timestamp and finalizer present\n328: - **WHEN** reconciling\n329: - **THEN** cleanup logic SHALL run first\n330: - AND finalizer SHALL be removed after cleanup succeeds\n331: \n332: #### Scenario: Finalizer removal error handling\n333: - **GIVEN** cleanup that fails\n334: - **WHEN** processing finalizer\n335: - **THEN** finalizer SHALL NOT be removed\n336: - AND reconciliation SHALL requeue with error\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ### Requirement: Scheme registration\n341: \n342: The system SHALL register custom resource types in the scheme.\n343: \n344: #### Scenario: Scheme registration\n345: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` and `groupversion_info.go`\n346: - **WHEN** setting up the reconciler\n347: - **THEN** `runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)` SHALL be called\n348: - AND `corev1.AddToScheme(scheme)` SHALL be called for Pod types\n349: \n350: #### Scenario: Scheme from client-go\n351: - **GIVEN** `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme`\n352: - **WHEN** using the scheme\n353: - **THEN** `Scheme` and `Codecs` SHALL be available from `register.go`\n354: - AND types SHALL be registered for `runtime/v1alpha1`\n355: \n356: ---\n357: \n358: ### Requirement: Concurrent reconciliation safety\n359: \n360: The system SHALL handle concurrent reconciliations safely.\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: Same resource concurrent reconcile\n363: - **GIVEN** two reconcile requests for the same resource\n364: - **WHEN** both execute concurrently\n365: - **THEN** only one SHALL proceed with status update\n366: - AND optimistic locking via `ResourceVersion` SHALL prevent conflicts\n367: \n368: #### Scenario: Conflict retry\n369: - **GIVEN** a status update that returns conflict error\n370: - **WHEN** retrying\n371: - **THEN** the resource SHALL be re-fetched\n372: - AND reconciliation SHALL retry with fresh data\n373: \n374: ---\n375: \n376: ### Requirement: Logger integration\n377: \n378: The system SHALL use structured logging for reconciliation.\n379: \n380: #### Scenario: Reconcile start logging\n381: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request\n382: - **WHEN** starting reconciliation\n383: - **THEN** `logger.Info(\"Reconciling\", \"kind\", kind, \"namespace\", namespace, \"name\", name)` SHALL be called\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: Reconcile error logging\n386: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation error\n387: - **WHEN** error occurs\n388: - **THEN** `logger.Error(err, \"Reconcile failed\", \"kind\", kind, \"namespace\", namespace, \"name\", name)` SHALL be called\n389: \n390: #### Scenario: Reconcile success logging\n391: - **GIVEN** a successful reconciliation\n392: - **WHEN** completing\n393: - **THEN** `logger.Info(\"Reconcile completed\", \"kind\", kind, \"namespace\", namespace, \"name\", name)` SHALL be called\n394: \n395: ---\n396: \n397: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Reconciler\n398: \n399: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for the reconciler.\n400: \n401: #### Scenario: Reconciler creation test\n402: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n403: - **WHEN** running tests\n404: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n405:   - NewReconciler returns valid instance\n406:   - All fields are properly initialized\n407: \n408: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime test\n409: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n410: - **WHEN** running tests\n411: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n412:   - AgentRuntime fetch succeeds\n413:   - Status updates are called correctly\n414:   - Conditions are set properly\n415: \n416: #### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter test\n417: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n418: - **WHEN** running tests\n419: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n420:   - CodeInterpreter fetch succeeds\n421:   - Warm pool pods are created/deleted as needed\n422:   - Status updates are called correctly\n423: \n424: #### Scenario: Not found handling test\n425: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n426: - **WHEN** running tests\n427: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n428:   - NotFound error returns empty result\n429:   - Cleanup is triggered for deleted resources\n430: \n431: #### Scenario: Status conflict test\n432: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n433: - **WHEN** running tests\n434: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n435:   - Conflict error triggers retry\n436:   - Resource is re-fetched on conflict\n437: \n438: ---\n439: \n440: ### Requirement: Integration tests for Reconciler\n441: \n442: The system SHALL have integration tests with fake clients.\n443: \n444: #### Scenario: Full reconciliation flow test\n445: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n446: - **WHEN** running tests\n447: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n448:   - Informer factory starts correctly\n449:   - WaitForCacheSync returns true\n450:   - Reconcile is triggered on resource changes\n451:   - Status is updated correctly\n452: \n453: #### Scenario: Warm pool integration test\n454: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n455: - **WHEN** running tests\n456: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n457:   - Warm pool pods are created to match WarmPoolSize\n458:   - Warm pool pods have correct labels and annotations\n459:   - Excess pods are deleted when WarmPoolSize decreases\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: Deletion integration test\n462: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n463: - **WHEN** running tests\n464: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n465:   - All pods are deleted when runtime is deleted\n466:   - Finalizer is removed after cleanup\n467:   - Store entries are removed\n468: \n469: ---\n470: \n471: ### Requirement: Fake client usage in tests\n472: \n473: The system SHALL use fake clients from client-go library in tests.\n474: \n475: #### Scenario: Fake clientset creation\n476: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n477: - **WHEN** setting up tests\n478: - **THEN** `fake.NewSimpleClientset(objects)` from `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake` SHALL be used\n479: \n480: #### Scenario: Fake typed client\n481: - **GIVEN** test setup\n482: - **WHEN** creating fake typed client\n483: - **THEN** `fake_runtime_client.go`, `fake_agentruntime.go`, `fake_codeinterpreter.go` SHALL be available\n484: \n485: #### Scenario: Fake informer factory\n486: - **GIVEN** test setup\n487: - **WHEN** creating fake informer factory\n488: - **THEN** `informers/externalversions/factory.go` SHALL work with fake client\n489: \n490: ---\n491: \n492: ### Requirement: Constants and defaults\n493: \n494: The system SHALL define reconciler constants and defaults.\n495: \n496: #### Scenario: Reconcile intervals\n497: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n498: - **WHEN** reading constants\n499: - **THEN** `ReconcileErrorRetryInterval` SHALL be `1 * time.Minute`\n500: - AND `ReconcilePeriodicInterval` SHALL be `5 * time.Minute`\n501: \n502: #### Scenario: Finalizer name\n503: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n504: - **WHEN** reading constants\n505: - **THEN** `FinalizerName` SHALL be `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer\"`\n506: \n507: ---\n508: \n509: ### Requirement: Directory structure\n510: \n511: The system SHALL organize reconciler files correctly.\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: Reconciler file location\n514: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n515: - **WHEN** listing files\n516: - **THEN** `reconciler.go` SHALL exist with `Reconciler` implementation\n517: \n518: #### Scenario: Reconciler test file location\n519: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n520: - **WHEN** listing files\n521: - **THEN** `reconciler_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n522: \n523: #### Scenario: Controller setup file location\n524: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n525: - **WHEN** listing files\n526: - **THEN** `controller.go` SHALL exist with controller setup functions\n527: \n528: ---\n529: \n530: ## Implementation Files\n531: \n532: | File | Purpose |\n533: |------|---------|\n534: | `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go` | Reconciler implementation |\n535: | `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go` | Reconciler unit tests |\n536: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller.go` | Controller setup and manager integration |\n537: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller_test.go` | Controller setup tests |\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Dependencies\n542: \n543: | Package | Purpose |\n544: |---------|---------|\n545: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned` | Typed client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n546: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions` | SharedInformerFactory |\n547: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1` | AgentRuntimeLister, CodeInterpreterLister |\n548: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Reconciler interface, ControllerManager |\n549: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API client |\n550: | `k8s.io/client-go/tools/record` | EventRecorder |\n551: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Pod types |\n552: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | Scheme |\n553: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | Conditions, ObjectMeta |\n554: \n555: ---\n556: \n557: ## Client-go Integration Points\n558: \n559: | Component | Source File | Usage |\n560: |-----------|-------------|-------|\n561: | Typed client | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/` | Get, Update, UpdateStatus, Delete |\n562: | Informer factory | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | Start, WaitForCacheSync |\n563: | AgentRuntime informer | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | Informer(), Lister() |\n564: | CodeInterpreter informer | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | Informer(), Lister() |\n565: | AgentRuntime lister | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | List, Get |\n566: | CodeInterpreter lister | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | List, Get |\n567: | Fake clientset | `clientset/versioned/fake/` | Unit test mock |\n568: | Scheme | `clientset/versioned/scheme/` | Resource encoding |\n569: \n570: ---\n571: \n572: ## Reconcile Result Values\n573: \n574: | Result | Requeue | RequeueAfter | Use Case |\n575: |--------|---------|--------------|----------|\n576: | `{}` | false | 0 | Completed, no further action |\n577: | `{Requeue: true}` | true | 0 | Immediate retry |\n578: | `{RequeueAfter: 1m}` | true | 1m | Error retry with delay |\n579: | `{RequeueAfter: 5m}` | true | 5m | Periodic check |\n580: \n581: ---\n582: \n583: ## Condition Types and Reasons\n584: \n585: | Condition Type | Reason | Status | Description |\n586: |----------------|--------|--------|-------------|\n587: | `Ready` | `Running` | True | Runtime ready to serve |\n588: | `Ready` | `Creating` | False | Runtime being created |\n589: | `Progressing` | `Creating` | True | Creation in progress |\n590: | `Progressing` | `Updating` | True | Update in progress |\n591: | `Available` | `Running` | True | Runtime available |\n592: | `Degraded` | `Error` | True | Runtime has errors |\n593: | `SessionActive` | `SessionStarted` | True | Active session |\n594: | `SessionActive` | `SessionEnded` | False | No active session |\n595: \n596: ---\n597: \n598: ## Event Types\n599: \n600: | Event Type | Reason | Message Pattern |\n601: |------------|--------|-----------------|\n602: | Normal | Created | \"Runtime created successfully\" |\n603: | Normal | Updated | \"Runtime updated successfully\" |\n604: | Normal | SessionStarted | \"Session started\" |\n605: | Normal | SessionEnded | \"Session ended: <reason>\" |\n606: | Warning | Error | \"<error message>\" |\n607: \n608: ---\n609: \n610: ## Warm Pool Labels and Annotations\n611: \n612: | Key | Value | Purpose |\n613: |-----|-------|---------|\n614: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member` | `\"true\"` | Mark pod as warm pool member |\n615: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime` | `<name>` | Reference to CodeInterpreter |\n616: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind` | `\"CodeInterpreter\"` | Owner kind |\n617: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` | `\"code-interpreter\"` | Sandbox type |\n618: \n619: ---\n620: \n621: ## Validation Checklist\n622: \n623: - [ ] Reconciler struct defined with all required fields\n624: - [ ] NewReconciler constructor initializes all fields\n625: - [ ] Reconcile method implements reconcile.Reconciler interface\n626: - [ ] AgentRuntime informer registered with event handlers\n627: - [ ] CodeInterpreter informer registered with event handlers\n628: - [ ] WaitForCacheSync called before reconciliation\n629: - [ ] Status updates use UpdateStatus method\n630: - [ ] Conditions set with proper Type, Status, Reason, Message\n631: - [ ] AgentRuntimeLister used for cached lookups\n632: - [ ] CodeInterpreterLister used for cached lookups\n633: - [ ] Pod lister used for sandbox pod lookup\n634: - [ ] Warm pool pods created/deleted to match WarmPoolSize\n635: - [ ] Events recorded for lifecycle changes\n636: - [ ] Requeue intervals configured appropriately\n637: - [ ] ControllerManager setup implemented\n638: - [ ] Watches configured for CRDs and Pods\n639: - [ ] Finalizer added on creation\n640: - [ ] Finalizer processed on deletion\n641: - [ ] Scheme registered with runtime/v1alpha1 and corev1\n642: - [ ] Conflict retry handles optimistic locking\n643: - [ ] Logger integration with structured logging\n644: - [ ] Fake clientset used in unit tests\n645: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n646: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n647: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n648: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n\n(End of file - total 648 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Kubernetes Reconciler controller that watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources, maintains desired state by managing sandbox pods, updates resource status conditions, and integrates with the informer framework from the generated client-go library.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Reconciler type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `Reconciler` as a Kubernetes controller for reconciling AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775847564277,"end":1775847564306}}}}
